# Tim Ferris 17 questions - Testing The “Impossible”
https://tim.blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/17-Questions-That-Changed-My-Life.pdf

## 1. What if I do the opposite of what everyone's doing (e.g. for 48 hours)?

## 2. What do I spen d a silly amount of money on? How might I scratch my own itch?

## 3. What would I do/have/be if I had $10 million? What’s my real TMI (target monthly income)?

## 4. What are the worst things that could happen? Could I get back here?

## 5. If I could only work 2 hours per week on my business, what would I do?

## 6. What if I let them make decisions up to $100? $500? $1,000 (progressively)?

## 7. What’s the least crowded channel?


## 8. What if I couldn’t pitch my product directly?
Sell stories, not products

## 9. What if I created my own real-world MBA?
How to spend money on learning in real world?

## 10. Do I need to make it back the way I lost it ?

## 11. What if I could only subtract (remove) to solve problems?

## 12. What might I put in place to allow me to go off the grid for 4 to 8 weeks, with no phone or email?

## 13. Am I hunting antelope or field mice?
“Did I spend today chasing mice or hunting antelope?”

## 14. Could it be that everything is fine and complete as is?

## 15. What would this look like if it were easy?

## 16. How can I throw money at this problem? How can I “waste” money to improve the quality of my life?

## 17. No hurry, no pause.

## Summary
Look for simple solutions.  If the answer isn’t simple, it’s probably not the right answer.

# Maciej Wieczorek 
## Recommended book: "Thinking through questions" by Anthony Weston

# Questions
## 1. What's the bottleneck of my company?
## 2. Whom can I outsource it to?
## 3. Is what I'm doing today making my goals real?
## 4. Is what I'm doing today pleasant,  improving my skills and making me happy? If not, what should I change?
## 5. Is it scalable? Can I make it 10x, 100x?
## 6. How can I give to my customers even more?
## 7. How can I make my coworkers/workers feel appreciated?
## 8. What are the best things my competition is doing?
## 9. What are the best and smarterst things my competition in other countries is doing?
## 10. Why am I doing/should I do this?
## 11. Which constant costs can I get rid of?
## 12. How can I do it quicker or not do it at all?
## 13. How to sell more? (upsell, cross sell, downsell)
## 13. How to increase customer LTV (lifetime value)?
## 14. How can I pay less taxes doing X?
## 15. What productivity technique can I start doing (for my or my teammates)?
## 16. What seems to be so ridiculous it might work out great?
## 17. What has no one in my industry done yet?
## 18. How to invest money from customers to double it?
## 19. Is my net worth bigger than X time ago? (e.g. one year ago and why)
## 20. What can go wrong and how can I prepare for that?
